<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-07-25T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-07-25T15:00:00-05:00" n="730" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d730">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/2618: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Consul at Harbin</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Hanson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-07-25T16:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">July 25,
                                        1922—4 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>For Stevens: Your July 22, 4 p.m. received and contents carefully
                            noted.</p>
                        <p>Situation is certainly fraught with difficulty but I am convinced that we
                            have adopted the only course possible under the circumstances. Your
                            observations and recommendations are always welcome and I shall keep you
                            advised of developments.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>